HEADWORD: Dromatherium
<hw>Drom`a*the"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>droma`s</grk> running + <grk>qhri`on</grk> beast. See
<er>Dromedary</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A small extinct
Triassic mammal from North Carolina, the earliest yet found in
America.</def>⟦br⟧
